parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, causing the vehicle to stall or stop running, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially if it occurs on a busy highway.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
and may exhibit symptoms such as a burning smell
and low oil pressure warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Oil Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure due to oil leaks can cause the vehicle to stall or stop running, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially if it occurs on a busy highway. Additionally, oil leaks can cause a fire hazard.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit symptoms such as a burning smell
and engine noise or knocking sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Camshaft Carrier and Head Gaskets
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft carrier and head gaskets can cause oil leaks, leading to engine failure, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially if it occurs on a busy highway. Additionally, oil leaks can cause a fire hazard.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit symptoms such as a burning smell
and engine noise or knocking sounds.
